Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) is an important characterization technique for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs); however, the overlap or dispersion in the frequency domain among physically distinct processes imposes great difficulties on unambiguous interpretation of EIS data.
Titulo: Modeling approach to identify physically distinct processes convoluted in electrochemical impedance spectra for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Built upon mechanistic SOFC model development and calibrations using polarization curve and multiple EIS curves under different operating voltages, a process reduction strategy was studied to identify both magnitude and frequencies of physically distinct processes convoluted in EIS.
Titulo: Modeling approach to identify physically distinct processes convoluted in electrochemical impedance spectra for proton-conducting solid oxide fuel cells
